The paper discusses compressive sensing (CS) in the context of parameter estimation tasks, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The use of structured sparsity models and clustering algorithms also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes the use of earth mover's distance (EMD) as a metric, which is commonly used in similarity and distance measures (cs.SI).
